    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Normal

        public static final JoinTypeEnum Normal
        A normal join. The output is the combination of the left and right hand solutions. Only solutions which join are output.

      • Optional

        public static final JoinTypeEnum Optional
        An optional join. The output is the combination of the left and right hand solutions. Solutions which join are output, plus any left solutions which did not join. Constraints on the join ARE NOT applied to the "optional" path.

      • Exists

        public static final JoinTypeEnum Exists
        A join where the left solution is output iff there exists at least one right solution which joins with that left solution. For each left solution, that solution is output either zero or one times. In order to enforce this cardinality constraint, the hash join logic winds up populating the "join set" and then outputs the join set once all solutions which join have been identified.

      • NotExists

        public static final JoinTypeEnum NotExists
        A join where the left solution is output iff there is no right solution which joins with that left solution. This basically an optional join where the solutions which join are not output.

        Note: This is also used for "MINUS" since the only difference between "NotExists" and "MINUS" deals with the scope of the variables.

      • Filter

        public static final JoinTypeEnum Filter
        A distinct filter (not a join). Only the distinct left solutions are output. Various annotations pertaining to JOIN processing are ignored when the hash index is used as a DISTINCT filter.
